  "texts": [
    "F is a full possibility frame in which ⟨S ⊥, ⊑ ⊥ ⟩ is a complete Boolean lattice.Proof.",
    "It suffices to show that if ⟨S ⊥, ⊑ ⊥ ⟩ is a complete Boolean lattice, then the set of principal downsets in ⟨S, ⊑⟩ plus ∅, which is P in a principal frame, is exactly the set of all X ⊆ S satisfying persistence and refinability in ⟨S, ⊑⟩, which is P in a full frame.",
    "If ⟨S ⊥, ⊑ ⊥ ⟩ is a Boolean lattice, then ⟨S, ⊑⟩ is separative by Fact 4.40, so every principal downset satisfies not only persistence but also refinability by Fact 4.6.1; and of course ∅ satisfies persistence and refinability.",
    "In the other direction, suppose X ⊆ S satisfies persistence and refinability.",
    "If X = ∅, we are done, so suppose X ̸ = ∅."
